summary: An ordinance submitting to the qualified voters of the City of Seattle, at the general election to be held in such city on March 7, 1911, the proposition of the issuance and sale by said city of its negotiable bonds in the sum of $70,000 to provide money for the acquisition, by purchase or condemnation, of a site in the vicinity of 23rdAvenue and Yesler Way, in said city and the construction thereon of a branch library building.
